abstract.gco:CharacterString: Statewide coverage of 1950 Places based on population data available from the U.S. Bureau of the Census. Population data is from Report of the Seventeenth Decennial Census of the United States (1950 Census of Population)

purpose.gco:CharacterString: To use in GIS systems for historical study and analysis This datasets is made available to interested persons through the University of Arizona's instance of Open Geoportal. It has been provided to assist educators, students, researchers, and policy makers in mapping and/or analysis applications.

credit.gco:CharacterString: Chris Kollen, University of Arizona Library

title.gco:CharacterString: REQUIRED: Reference to a formally registered thesaurus or a similar authoritative source of theme keywords.

environmentDescription.gco:CharacterString: Microsoft Windows XP Version 5.1 (Build 2600) Service Pack 2; ESRI ArcCatalog 9.2.2.1350

measureDescription.gco:CharacterString: Digitized city boundaries from the following maps: Amphitheatre used Census descriptions of geographic subdivisions and enumeration districts 1830-1950; Avondale, Buckeye, Chandler, Gilbert, Glendale, Goodyear, Mesa, Phoenix, Tempe, Tolleson, and Wickenburg used Maricopa County Annexation File; Bisbee used Bisbee, 1947 (Sanborn); Casa Grande used City of Casa Grande, 1955; Clifton used Map of Greenlee County, 1916 (no changes until 1970); Coolidge used Coolidge, Arizona, 1956; Douglas used Douglas, 1947 (Sanborn); Duncan used Duncan, 1950; Flagstaff used City of Flagstaff, a planning and zoning map for annexation; Globe used Globe, 1948 (Sanborn) and Globe 7.5' topographic quadrangle, 1947; Hayden used Hayden Townsite, 1956; Holbrook used Holbrook, Arizona 1949; Kingman used City of Kingman, 1950; Miami used Miami 1948 (Sanborn); Nogales used City of Nogales, 1951; Parker used Plot of the Townsite of Parker, 1956; Pima used Map of Pima, Territory of Arizona, County of Graham, 1887 (no changes until 1960); Prescott used City of Prescott Annexation History, 2007; Safford used Official Map of the Town of Safford and Additions, April-May 1916 (no changes until 1960); Somerton used City of Somerton Annexation map; South Tucson used Tucson Annexation Boundary File; Thatcher used Official Map of Thatcher, 1902 (no changes until 1970); Tombstone used Tombstone, Arizona, 1882 (Sanborn; no changes until 1960); Tucson used Tucson Annexation Boundary File; Wakefield and West Yuma used Arizona minor civil divisions--supervisorial districts, 1950; Willcox used Willcox, 1956, Cochise and Willcox 15' topographic quadrangle, 1958; Williams used Plot of Williams townsite and additions, 1949; Winslow used City of Winslow, 1950; and Yuma used City of Yuma Annexation map. For remaining places, used Geographic Names Information System database for point data. Created a 200 meter buffer around all point data in order to convert into polygons.

value.gco:Record: Accuracy ranges from ~10 meters (Scale 1:1800) to ~1 km. (Scale 1:750,000)

description.gco:CharacterString: Dataset renamed from 1950_Cities.shp to Arizona_CensusPlaces_1950.shp by Ben Hickson with the University of Arizona Library. Metadata fields corresponding the Open Geoportal Working Group Best Practices Guide (http://opengeoportal.org/working-groups/metadata/) were also updated.
